				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ {\beta}_{ck}^{(I)} $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M38" display="inline"><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>β</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">ck</mml:mi><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mi>I</mml:mi></mml:mfenced></mml:msubsup></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13059_2020_2126_Article_IEq16.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>. We solve the above model using least squares which provides estimates for the regression coefficients and their statistical significance via <italic>P</italic> values <inline-formula id="IEq17"><alternatives><tex-math id="M39">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
